decklists.title: A Song of Turns and Dongers

description: A deck based around playing small creatures with evasion and chaining extra turns.
title: [HISTORIC] Edric Turns

description: A fast deck which combos using Food Chain, with good matchups vs control/stax. Over the years, FC started to see repeated power creep, with commanders requiring less pieces to close out games.
title: [HISTORIC] Food Chain History

description: A powerful and resilient combo deck aimed at maximizing deck speed, individual card strength, and value-scaling as the game progresses.
title: Thrasios Tymna Midrange

description: A creature based stax deck that seeks to slow the game down and hate out its opponents. Eventually winning with a one card combo with the commander. The deck is very resilient to creature removal and packs a punch as you constantly threaten life totals with your slowly growing creatures.
title: Heliod Ballista

description: Tymna Kraum Breach focuses on quickly assembling wincons with one card enablers such as Ad Nauseam or Intuition. The deck puts a heavy emphasis on Ad Nauseam, Underworld Breach, and Dockside Extortionist flickers. Tymna Kraum Breach utilizes a lot of fast mana to power out either explosive wins or strong early card advantage engines such as Kraum or Rhystic Study. Tymna Kraum Breach usually seeks to be the fastest deck at the table, but it has the potential to grind when needed.
title: Kraum Tymna Breach

description: A sans-red version of midrange Ad-Naus, with asymmetrical hate pieces and more storm.
title: [HISTORIC] Thrasios Tymna E-MAN

description: An adaptive combo list focused on assembling a combo using Elsha and Sensei's Divining Top, as well as utilizing Underworld Breach lines. The deck utilizes the strong card advantage engine and flexibility in timing that Elsha's ability provides to progress its own gameplan while hindering others. The list boasts high card quality due to the winconless nature of its combos, allowing it to run a strong suite of interaction.
title: Elsha Top

description: Oracle Hulk is a Flash Hulk deck that combines the historic speed and efficiency of Flash as a win condition, with the card quality and resilience of Consultation to deadly effect. Oracle Hulk is equally capable of keeping up with the fastest of the fast, as well as out-grinding the best of them. The deck is incredibly difficult to meaningfully disrupt, and will compete at the top level in all but the most hostile metas.
title: [HISTORIC] Thrasios Tymna Flash Hulk

description: An extremely proactive list, bringing Anje out as quickly as possible to filter through the 40% of the deck that is Madness cards. The density of Madness cards means that the deck is effectively a 60-card deck, increasing its consistency. The deck finishes people off through Worldgorger Dragon loops with Anje out to draw the deck or occasionally infinite mana combos with Cloudstone Curio, again filtering through Anje to find a finisher.
title: Anje Madness

description: An all-in fast combo list which chains Arcum's ability using Paradox/Flute.
title: [HISTORIC] Paradox Arcum

description: You play your commander as soon as possible, and accrue an ever increasing amount of warriors until you can find a way to generate infinite mana using these tokens, which results in infinite combats using Najeela‚Äôs ability. Often enough, the warriors themselves already do the trick.
title: Najeela Tempo

description: This deck wins by looping Gray Merchant or "storming" off with lifegain engines in play. It get's to run a lot of high CMC tutors and interesting cards not found in other black cEDH decks thanks to K'rrik's unique form of "mana ramp". It can consistently threaten turn 3-5 wins with multiple one card win-con enablers. K'rrik's best matchups are playing into stax and in pods that lack countermagic and/or graveyard hate.
title: K'rrik, Son of Yawgmoth

description: Rakdos Worldgorger decks leverage Black's tutor suite and the availability of cheap outlet commanders to assemble the Worldgorger Dragon combo. Decks often feature anti-meta disruptive elements such as creature hate and hand hate.
title: [HISTORIC] Xantcha WGD

description: 5c reanimator focusing on Worldgorger Dragon and Razaketh
title: [HISTORIC] Scion Reanimator

description: A sans-white version of typical sans-red Thassa's Oracle decks. While these highly adaptive, interactive decks can win quickly with infinite mana or Underworld Breach. These decks look to establish card advantage early and interact on the stack. They have no issue easily pivoting to a grind strategy, falling back on Thrasios, Triton Hero and Seedborn Muse to pull ahead and win with an efficient combo finish.
title: Thrasios Vial Midrange

description: The goal of Azami Turns is to survive the early game through the use of efficient countermagic and permanent-based disruption, prolonging the game enough to establish control by leveraging Azami as a stifling card advantage engine. Eventually once a commanding position has been established the game can be ended using an extra turn loop combo, ideally with multiple pieces of protection.
title: Azami Wizards

description: A fast and graveyard-reliant combo deck which layers together multiple win conditions, often including Hermit Druid, Food Chain, and sometimes other options like Reanimator, Protean Hulk, and Doomsday.
title: [HISTORIC] Sidisi Layered Combo

description: A potent midrange deck which slows others down with stax while making big mana.
title: Teferi Chain Veil

description: Zur Consultation leverages the ability for Zur to fetch Necropotence as well as threaten wins from hand with Ad Nauseam and Demonic Consultation. Shimmer versions of the list are able to win at instant speed with Shimmer Myr after paying a large amount of life to Necropotence
title: Zur Consultation

description: Tayam is a creature-based midrange combo deck that can combo with Devoted Druid and a pump spell to combo. Tayam decks may additional leverage common GBW strengths such as Ad Nauseam, Hatebears, and Reanimation to win. Tayam decks are usually best suited for grindy pods but suffer from board wipes and may rely on Tayam to be in play.
title: Tayam Midrange

description: Sisay is a proactive deck that utilizes Sisay's unique activated ability to tutor essential pieces for winning the game. Some lists also utilize Jegantha as a 5C dork in the companion zone to enable a powerful 2-part combo with Sisay.
title: Sisay Midrange Tutors

description: This is a fast combo deck that seeks to layer Food Chain, and Consultation strategies. Like most fast combo decks, we are seeking to win as fast as possible, forgoing some of the value mid-range cards for aggressive tutors. The commander is here primarily as an outlet for Food Chain. The deck contains the very best cards in BUG, which happens to be the three best colors in cEDH.
title: Cazur Ukkima Food Chain

description: 5 Color Storm is an archetype that combines the best tutors, acceleration, and combo enablers in every color to assemble powerful storm turns often involving Ad Nauseam, Yawg Will, Breach, and 2-card combos such as Consultation.
title: [HISTORIC] Golos Storm

description: A draw-go control list which uses Rashmi to generate card advantage for counterspells.
title: Rashmi Control

description: A fast and cheap combo deck with high variance, fat creatures, and big mana.
title: Selvala Brostorm

description: A Protean Hulk/Reanimator deck which uses Mimeoplasm as a backup reanimator.
title: [HISTORIC] Mimeo Reanimator Hulk

description: Kess uses the turbo Grixis cards such as Ad Nauseam and Peer into the Abyss to draw into their combos, most often involving Underworld Breach and Thassa's Oracle. The other pieces, Demonic Consultation and Tainted pact, of the latter combo can be used with the commander as a "one card win condition" as they can both find the oracle and exile your library. Compared to many other Grixis lists, Kess doesn't usually play a lot of unique cards or combos.
title: Kess Naus

description: A stormish deck which focuses on using Thrasios as both a noninfinite and infinite sink.
title: [HISTORIC] Thrasios Vial Paradox Scepter

description: Marwyn Elfball is a proactive deck that plays very similarly to Selvala Brostorm. With nearly 30 creatures, over half of which are Elves, Marwyn aims to assemble a storm-like win using pump spells and a critical mass of Elves with win conditions seen in most typical mono green cEDH decks.
title: Marwyn Elfball

description: A fast and consistent combo list which is highly interactive and difficult to shut down.
title: First Sliver Food Chain

description: A proactive deck that seeks to win the game as quickly as possible. Utilizes the commander as a strong value engine to assemble its resilient and dedicated combo with a discard outlet and Dakmor Salvage.
title: Gitrog Dakmor Combo

description: A mono-red ramp list which assembles an infinite combo off of only its commander.
title: Godo Helm

decklists.title: Combo? Where We're Going, We Don't Need Combo

description: Nath is a midrange stax list focused on discarding, mana denial, and staying ahead of the ‚Äústax curve‚Äù while your opponents lose resources. The deck typically seeks to set up a stax‚Äôd out boardstate and end the game with a finisher such as the SquirrelCraft combo, beats, or in some lists, Razaketh. As a slower deck, there can be struggle against turbo strategies but excels if you can reel them in to Nath's pace.
title: [HISTORIC] Nath Stax

description: Emry is a non-linear combo deck with varying gameplay patterns and a high learning curve. This deck utilizes the graveyard by repeatedly using Emry's ability to cycle artifacts through your graveyard, using Emry-specific combos and more traditional Isochron Scepter combos in a controlling shell.
title: Emry Artifacts

description: Kroxa adds a unique flavor to the world of Rakdos cEDH in that he is both an outlet in the command zone and does not require activated abilities to win. Kroxa's win condition will require only one card in hand (Animate Dead) and one card in the graveyard (Worldgorger Dragon), allowing the pilot to continue the game unhindered if hands are attacked or the game state is reduced to top-decking.
title: Kroxa Hand Control

description: Marath Holy Trinity is a stax deck that seeks to assemble the ‚Äúholy trinity‚Äù of stax pieces: Linvala, Keeper of Silence, Living Plane and Collector Ouphe to completely lock down your opponents‚Äô ability to cast spells. In the meantime, Marath is a powerful tool for controlling the board, picking off mana dorks and small commanders with ease. Powerful support cards like Unbound Flourishing, Earthcraft and Dockside Extortionist eventually become combo pieces to put the game away.
title: [HISTORIC] Marath Stax

description: Turbo-Ad Nauseam list which is capable of explosively fast storm wins.
title: [HISTORIC] Sidisi Ad Naus Fishbowl

description: An adaptive, efficient, and consistent mono green list designed to combo out with typical green infinite mana combos assembled through Yisan's ability. This deck is a bit slower, which is made possible by tutorable hate pieces like Collector Ouphe to take the game into the later turns. There it can take up a beatdown plan, swinging in with powerful green creatures.
title: Yisan Midrange

description: Inalla is a proactive combo deck with multiple one card win conditions backed up by the proven and powerful consultation package. What Inalla lacks in command zone value and the utility white or green provides decks, she makes up for with absolutely blistering speed backed up by an interaction suite rivaling that of many of the format's most controlling decks.
title: Inalla Wizard Combo

decklists.title: b i r d w i z a r d

description: A stax deck that uses Derevi‚Äôs abilities coupled with bears to assemble mana-denial locks.
title: [HISTORIC] Derevi Stax

description: Kinnan is a proactive/midrange deck that aims to utilize Kinnan to generate lots of mana and then funnel that mana into payoffs such as tutors or draw spells. Kinnan seeks to assemble infinite mana with combos such as Isochron Scepter + Dramatic Revelation and Basalt Monolith + Kinnan. It then uses Kinnan to find true outlets such as Thrasios to draw the deck and finish everyone off.
title: Kinnan Infinite Mana

description: KCI Teshar is a unique fast combo deck based on artifacts and highly synergistic and complex to pilot, based on the graveyard recursion ability of Teshar, Ancestor's Apostle. It has several overlapping redundant combo pieces, giving the necessary consistency to reach the numerous possibilities involving looping artifacts to win the game quickly and with some security against common disrupts such as counters and artifact removals, due to recursion provided by the commander.
title: Teshar KCI

description: A Paradox Engine combo deck which can switch between fast combo and stax gameplans.
title: [HISTORIC] Sisay Paradox

description: Niv-Mizz Parun Control, is a control shell similar to Rashmi, Curious Control, and Tasigur that seeks to slow the game down with Stax, prevent wins with interaction, and eventually end the game with a resolved Niv Mizzet. Compact combos include Curiosity effect on Niv-Mizzet, or sometimes with Glint-Horn Buccaneer or Isochron Scepter + Dramatic Reversal. Does poorly against multiple fast, low-interaction, decks. Does well against mid-range or other control lists.
title: Niv-Mizzet Parun Control

description: Yuriko is a deck that utilizes Yuriko's ability to burn out its opponents while maintaining card advantage using enablers (low costing creatures) and ninjas. The versatile deck shifts between playing Aggro, Combo, and Control. The deck wins by burning your opponents' life totals to zero, Thoracle + Consultation/Pact, Nashi + Enter the Infinite, or Sakashima's Student loop with an opponent's Dockside. Yuriko is incredibly resilient due to her Commander Ninjutsu which bypasses Commander Tax.
title: Yuriko Tempo

description: A low-curve, engine-oriented combo shell for Yarok that leverages cards like Cloud of Faeries, Aluren, Earthcraft and Intruder Alarm to net infinite mana off of continuous creature casts, which are fueled by bounce outlets such as Shrieking Drake, Cavern Harpy, or Cloudstone Curio. Combined with an ETB draw creature like Wall of Blossoms, the deck can then win with a win card of your choice, usually with a large Finale of Devastation, Laboratory Maniac or an established Timetwister loop.
title: Yarok Spellseeker Aluren

description: This Jund turbo list seeks to leverage payoffs like Necropotence and Ad Nauseam to propel itself into one of its many 2 or 3 card combos. Korvold specifically supports many aristocrat-style combos that serve to draw through the deck on pace with other black payoffs, as well as provide additional resiliency when it comes to winning. While it focuses on the early game, the deck can also take to the late game by keeping its hand full with Korvold's ability and swinging in with a large Korvold to put pressure on its opponents.
title: Korvold Turbo Sacrifice

description: Tymna/Tana Hulk is a proactive archetype that cheats Protean Hulk into play using the former Shuffle Hulk package. While it doesn't have the speed of Varolz Hulk nor the power of the Oracle pile, the deck has a strong source of card advantage in Tymna, can power out explosive turns with Dockside Extortionist, and has additional ways of getting Hulk triggers using cards like Sneak Attack and Goblin Bombardment
title: Tana Tymna Protean Hulk

description: Kenrith Midrange is an adaptive deck that wants to out-value other decks through multiple lines that generate card value. Typical wincons include Oracle Consult and Dockside Mayhem loops with Kenrith.
title: Kenrith Midrange

description: Winota Snowball Stax seeks to be an explosive stax combo deck that wants to play nonhuman creatures early and then play its commander. Winota cheats creatures into play at an alarming rate, and the deck can overwhelm the board quite easily. The explosive nature of the deck in combination with its tightly layered combos allows for the first real opportunity for Boros to play at the competitive tables.
title: Winota Stax

description: A proactive Doomsday deck that utilizes its commander to crack the piles, to win with Kiki-Jiki and Zealous Conscripts, with a variety of backup win conditions, such Redcap combo or Snoop lines. The deck's primary goal is to make a lot of fast mana and utilize it to make explosive plays.
title: Grenzo Doomsday

decklists.title: üåä Urza Poly Tyrant üåä"The Tide pod Challenge"üåÄ

description: Urza, Lord High Artificer leverages fast artifact mana and wincons such as Isochron Scepter + Dramatic Reversal, and Power Artifact + Grim Monolith. Additionally, Urza has the unique benefit of breaking parity with mana denial stax pieces such as Static Orb and Winter Orb. The Poly versions look to win with Polymorph / Proteus Staff getting Hullbreaker Horror to generate infinite mana.
title: Urza Infinite Mana

description: Malcom // Vial Smasher is a traditional grixis turbo naus shell with additional wincons of Malcom + Glint Horn Buccaneer. Malcolm is very cheap to play and helps with initial ramp needed to get off the ground in the early game.
title: Malcolm Vial Turbo Naus

description: A quick combo deck with the goal of assembling any infinite mana combo or doing normal Jeskai Breach shenanigans with Intuition.
title: Jeska Ishai Murderbird

description: This is a turbo ad nauseam deck that uses its 0 mana commander to enable cards that are incredibly good in the archetype at a very early turn (e.g.: Mox Amber, Culling the Weak, Fierce Guardianship). The deck is incredibly fast, even when compared to other turbo naus commanders. The downside is that it loses out on a commander that grants card advantage.
title: Rograkh Silas Turbo Naus

description: Rakdos turbo naus is a proactive rakdos storm deck that uses Rog to enable a variety of additional fast mana and gas cards or Jeska as a removal piece or infinite mana outlet, in addition to leveraging Tevesh as a card advantage engine.
title: Rakdos Turbo Naus

description: Tasigur has the ability to power out early game wins while pivoting to a bevy of secondary strategies if disrupted, giving the deck near-unparalleled flexibility. You can grind with many of the best decks at the table and land a stupid value engine early, whether through a powerful Ad Nauseam or a combo utilizing Tasigur's cost reduction to power out expensive creatures through Evolution effects.
title: Tasigur

description: Orvar, the All-Form is a mono blue control deck that utilizes Orvar's token making to hold up interaction while allowing for instant speed ramping and board development using Twitch-style spells to generate value while maintaining card advantage, finishing the game with oddball Orvar-based combos.
title: Orvar Twitch Control

description: 4c combo machine focused on landing any number of Dockside Extortionist or Underworld Breach based combos. Essentially functioning on a Jeskai base with Green adding a solid amount of consistency with its creature tutors and general resilience.
title: Omnath 4 Colour Breach

description: Magda is a proactive midrange combo deck, with both stax and fast combo pivots. This Treasure centric deck, focuses on high synergies between treasure generators such as dockside (and your friendly friends from under the mountain) to leverage Magda, Brazen Outlaw's ability to tutor and combo off for the win. This is usually done with Clock of Omen's and an artifact dwarf, or several of the other 2 card combos within the deck.
title: Magda Clock Combo

description: This is a Sultai Midrange deck that uses its commanders as the main draw engine to find its combos and layers different combos to win the game. A potential main focus is Displacer Kitten to generate more mana for Thrasios activations or flickering Tevesh to draw more cards as well. In addition, it layers its small reanimation package for Hullbreaker Horror to generate infinite mana. Its main way of winning the game is Thassa's Oracle with Timetwister loop as the backup.
title: Tevesh Thrasios Midrange

description: Turbo ad nauseam mardu deck that leverages Rograkh to enable extremely fast starts and Tymna as a back up plan for grinding.
title: Rog Tymna Turbo Naus

description: A turbo Ad Nauseam strategy that uses Tymna as a value piece to stay relevant during the whole game while either having another combo piece in the command zone with Malcolm, or even more value with Sakashima. Missing red is going to make this deck slower compared to its Grixis counterparts as many rituals and wincons have been printed in this colour recently, but the UB core still allows us to go for very explosive wins especially considering many lists can pivot to a commander-centric plan.
title: Esper Turbo Naus

description: This is a manual storm deck that focuses on creating various engines(using its commanders and/or Magecraft creatures) to help you win the game. With an engine your ordinary spells can turn into game winning pieces. The deck has many layers and can fallback to some of the well known combos with Dualcaster Mage and Underworld Breach.
title: Krark Sakashima Clones

description: Koll is a fast layered combo deck focusing on abusing the interaction of cheap equipment, such as Skullclamp, alongside Koll to generate value and combo off. The main combo lines of the deck include looping Dockside Extortionist with Mortarpod and/or Skullclamp with a free creature. These are supported by various other situational combo lines, which layer alongside each other.
title: Koll Equipment Combo

decklists.title: Lil Saka & The East Tree Boyz

description: "Sakadama" is a proactive "trigger-storm" deck. It's a turn slower than most other proactive lists (3/4 instead of 2/3) but makes up for it by being HIGHLY resistant to stax.
title: Kodama Sakashima Storm

description: This deck attempts to land a Rule of Law effect as early as turn one or two to slow opponents down. From there we can play a turn three Tymna, which allows us to refill our hand and flood the board with more stax pieces until we can land Kodama and go for a win in the later game, around turn 6 or after. In comparison to other abzan stax builds, this deck struggles to win through tutor hate or Drannith Magistrate, and can struggle to stick Kodama before winning, but excels at winning through almost all other stax effects including our own.
title: Kodama Tymna Stax

description: A Grixis Ad Nauseam Storm / Breach deck that uses both of the commanders as card draw engines to help get us to a win. With Tevesh now at the helm, we can utilize our creatures beyond just the abilities in the card text. Not only is Tevesh itself an outlet, but other cards such as rituals, or tutors become more synergistic with our game plan. The aim here is to be drawing multiple cards on our turn to out advantage our opponents, and get us to the point of storming off.
title: Kraum Tevesh Breach Storm

description: This is a grindy, value-based deck that uses Ob Nixilis to generate card advantage. It uses cards like Kederekt Parasite to grind out long games. It can use Ob Nixilis‚Äô size to one-shot opponents. This deck is reliant on Ob Nixilis, but if you resolve him early, then you will find yourself winning several games. It is slower than ad naus decks and decks that run rograkh, but it sees a lot more cards. It also has the major upside of using all will be one as a one-card win.
title: Ob Nixilis Ping

description: Evolution is a mana combo deck with compact and overlapping cards to gain quality of cards and speed. Deck aims to win at medium speed with Thrasios activations into a lethal finale or a Timetwister loop of spells.
title: Bruse Thrasios Midrange

description: An adaptive combo deck that leverages the consistency and versatility of Captain Sisay's ability to assemble one-card combos and find silver bullet stax pieces to stop a majority of archetypes in the format. This deck aims to have Sisay in play quickly and tutor for stax pieces to lock out the board or tutor for infinite mana combos using a variety of legendary combo enablers, including Ashaya, Soul of the Wild, Emiel the Blessed, and Kogla, the Titan Ape. The deck can also assemble stax locks with Living Plane and Linvala, Keeper of Silence or Elesh Norn.
title: Sisay Adaptive Tutors

description: A deck that uses hate cards to lock other players out of their resources. The deck closes games with either one card combo Ardenn/Godo, punchies, or other options such as cloning Archon of Valor's Reach
title: Ardenn Tana Hatebears

description: This deck seeks to quickly assemble a variety of artifact-based infinite combos using Arcum's ability to fetch missing combo pieces. The deck can also pivot to instead using Arcum to power out an early back-breaking stax piece, navigate the early game and buy time to combo out.
title: Arcum Adaptive Combo

description: Enchanted Harvest's gameplan, similar to that of the legacy enchantress archetype, is to act as a pseudo-prision/stax deck. This is accomplished by abusing stong hate pieces like Stoney Silence and Drannith Magistrate to slow our opponent's gameplans. In doing this, we allow time to establish a value engine, such as our commander or another enchantress (e.g., Argothian Enchantress). A winning position usually involves a combo finisher, such as Nature's Chosen loops or Seedcradle Witch loops, allowing us to swing for lethal or draw our deck for a similar result.
title: Sythis Enchantments

description: This is a fast combo deck that leverages Gruul's creature tutors and your commander's card draw to crack snoop piles quickly, occasionally hiding behind hatebears and assembling creature based value engines.
title: Gruul Snoop

description: A mono white stax deck built around locking your opponents out and using Oswald Fiddlebender to break parity under Rule of Law effects and enable multi-piece combos that let you win through your own stax pieces.
title: Oswald Rule of Law Stax

description: Green-black hulk lists use their namesake card, protean hulk, in conjunction with their commander (usually a sacrifice outlet) to find a game-winning combo to put into play. The decks are usually fairly stax-resistant because little pieces interact with this combo. Because they lack colours as well as card advantage in the command zone they tend to interact unfavorably in very fast games due to the lack of stack interaction or very long games due to missing the ability to grind.
title: Golgari Hulk

description: A resilient Malcolm and GHB combo deck with alternative lines through underworld breach/LED/brain freeze, twinflame/DCM, and of course GHB/curiosity. Can win fast but also can grind value into late game.
title: Bruse Malcolm Glinthorn

description: Bant Advantage Evolution, the BAE archetype, seizes advantage by having a 1-CMC commander in the CZ, opening new Neoform lines into each of the deck's compact combos. While not combing off, the deck turns its other commander, Thrasios, into a grindy value engine, eventually overwhelming the board with filtered card draw and value.
title: Thrasios Yoshimaru Cradlestorm

description: Pacific Poly is a combo deck at heart that leverages the activated ability of Shorikai, Genesis Engine with cards such as Manifold Key that allow us to activate Shorikai more than once each turn to amass massive advantage and a perfectly sculpted hand. We make good use of heavy control and interactive elements, even including Humility, to keep opponents at bay until we‚Äôre able to pivot into our winning turn. This often involves getting infinite mana through Isochron Scepter and Hullbreaker Horror.
title: Shorikai Combo

description: This deck tries to cast a stax piece on the second turn of the game and follow it up with even more stax. Once the table is sufficiently held down, it casts Najeela to finish its opponents off either through just attacking or a one-card combo kill with Najeela. Najeela Stax struggles with card advantage on account of having none in the command zone. Decks with large amounts of creatures, card advantage, or board wipes can also give it fits. That said, it can run both Null Rod and Rule of Law effects (a rarity in this format), is able to run strong cards due to having all five colors, and has one of the strongest single-card wins in the command zone. It excels in metas with fast combo decks and/or other stax decks.
title: Najeela Stax

description: This list takes advantage of having a tutor in the command zone to assemble very flexible lines. Having a large number of one card win conditions, and the ability to find whatever you need means the list is very resilient and able to make multiple win attempts, even in the face of interaction.
title: Rocco Creature Tutor

description: This turbo deck utilizes it's commander to cast an early Ad Nauseam or aggressively loop spells from the graveyard to storm into a win via Brain Freeze or Thassa's oracle. It utilizes the graveyard heavily to be an incredibly fast and resilient Grixis deck with a unique twist over some of the other turbo naus decks around.
title: Cormela Turbo

description: Temur Thrasios Midrange aims at using both it's commanders to gain advantage over the table and use evolution pieces to go infinite with Dockside Extortionist. Typically turns 4-5 while holding up interaction on turns 3-4 to stop wins.
title: Temur Thrasios Midrange

description:
Tana Tymna Hulk is a midrange deck that seeks to slow down its opponents with its many supreme stax pieces until it finds a game ending combo involving Protean Hulk, or Arena and/or Academy Rector and Kiki-Jiki. 
The deck fuses together the very best from the well known Tymna&Tana Birthing Pod / Hulk lists. 

We want to deploy a RoL and/or Null Rod effect asap to slow down faster decks. Rector Breakers biggest strengths is the fact that we can combo off through Null Rod effects with Vivien on the Hunt instead of Birthing Pod. Having Tymna as our commander gives us huge grind potential as well. The most obvious weakness is not playing blue and not being super interactive on the first 2 turns.
title: Tana Tymna Midrange

description: This is a resilient Midrange Abzan deck that leverages the power of its commanders to draw and sacrifice a protean and control the board and pace of the game with Halana.
title: Halana Tymna Hulk

description: Sans-blue turbo lists are extremely fast combo decks intending to leverage early mana and wheels into Ad Naus or PITA. The inclusion of light grind pieces enables the deck a surprising mid game via the Tymna card draw or Bruse/Ikra lifegain plans, giving these decks staying power and stronger mulligan options. In comparison to sans-G turbo decks, green offers the obscene enabler of Culling Ritual, additional fast mana, and a stronger removal suite.
title: Tana Tymna Turbo Naus

description: Marneus Calgar is versatile against many deck archetypes and can evade the majority of concerning stax pieces. This is an opportunistic deck that seeks to control the game while generating card advantage over time or turbo aggressive win attempts. Marneus will keep the table in check time and time again!
title: Marneus Midrange

decklists.title: The Suite Life of Sacking Codie

description: The new Profane tutor utilizes Codie more often. We can use it to tutor bring to light/ad nauseam/peer using rituals such as Culling the weak/Burnt offering/Sacrifice etc. This is a 5c turbo naus deck at heart.
title: Codie Turbo Naus

description: A sans-white turbo Ad Nauseam strategy that focuses on powerful early starts to end the game quickly, focusing on the common grixis core of fast Ad Nauseam strategies in conjunction with Underworld Breach and Dockside Extortionist. When it is unable to win quickly, it can utilize the powerful card advantage engine Kraum provides while keeping Ad Nauseam relevant and lethal even in the later stages of the game through Ikra Shidiqi's lifegain.
title: Ikra Kraum Turbo Naus

description: A combo deck which uses a unique suite of combos with Animar's discount ability.
title: Animar Harvest

description: Atraxa is both a Food Chain combo outlet and a soft payoff in the command zone, meaning we can build a layered deck that supports both strategies, while also having some unique and powerful interactions with Atraxa herself, like Displacer Kitten. This deck lacks the early game value that Tymna and Thrasios can provide, but the rest of her textbox positions her well for longer games, where you are able to use her large body to pressure opposing life totals, threaten a three turn player clock under a staxxed board or replenish your life total for a late-game Ad Nauseam.
title: Atraxa Food Chain

description: Combo heavy midrange list which aims to overwhelm opponents with win conditions or grind with Thrasios. This list uses a variety of layered combos to gain advantage and win the game. It has a fantastic grind plan and can quickly pivot into a win when given a window. You should play this list if you like interactive gameplay, thought provoking non-repetitive combo lines, and grindy games.
title: Dargo Thrasios Combo Midrange

description: Minsc, Beloved Ranger provides multiple strategies utilizing the unique ability to "kill" your own creatures with Minsc's ability, allowing for decks that seek to cheat Protean Hulk or Academy Rector into play. The ability can also be used as an infinite mana outlet in slower builds available due to its Naya color identity.
title: Naya Minsc

description: This deck deploys creature- and enchantment-based static interaction, such as Archon of Emeria and Stony Silence, targeting the Dockside-Oracle-Breach metagame in the early turns. The commander immediately generates board presence that grows at a quadratic rate, and also draws cards through combat and enchantresses. Compared to other Green-White commanders, the combination of board presence and card advantage from Ellivere has the highest ceiling. While the deck plays well through Rule of Law and its own stax, it is slow to win without combos and susceptible to hard board wipes.
title: Ellivere Stax

description:
This is an adaptive control list that seeks to survive the early game by utilizing powerful hatepieces like Grafdigger's Cage or Cursed Totem that allow us to slow down our opponents so we can find a game ending combo. 
Due to Talions ability to draw cards we can make sure to not run out of ressources.
In comparison to other control decks like Tivit or Niv-Mizzet Parun it lacks clear one card wincons out of the CZ like Time Sieve or Curiosity.
title: Talion Control

description:
Tatyova Turns is a midrange deck that aims to navigate the early game through interaction and playing key stax pieces, and is able to dominate the mid-late game thanks to having a very powerful value engine on the command zone that is able to draw a lot of cards without casting spells and functions through the most commonly played stax. It wins through generating an infinite turns loop or with a huge finale of devastation after making infinite mana/drawing your deck. The primer has all the combo lines explained.

Tatyova is a deck that focuses on lands, which is a unique arquetype not commonly seen in cedh that can be attractive to players trying to start on the format or looking for an unconventional cedh deck. With this deck I won Ka0s Treasure Series 7 in September 2023, proving that it is a viable cedh deck in the current meta.
title: Tatyova Turns

commander.name: Heliod, the Radiant Dawn // Heliod, the Warped Eclipse

description: An Azorius Storm deck that utilizes flash and cost reduction to choose the best window to go off
title: Heliod Flash Storm

description: This deck uses the new Saheeli to provide lots of value by abusing a variety of cards that have enter or leave the battlefield effects. Because of this it has a variety of 1 card win conditions with saheeli and overlapping lines that provide lots of redundancy. The deck has two versions, one that is a little faster using underworld breach lines, and a version that is a little more slower that tries to abuse Coveted Jewel as a repeatable card draw and mana engine.
title: Saheeli Combo

description: Tameshi is a combo-control deck that uses its commander to present difficult to interact with wins and rebuy high impact permanents. The deck uses Lotus Bloom and LED to great effect, generating large bursts of mana to enable intricate combo turns. The high number of draw engines and interactive spells allows the deck to consistently play into a wide variety of metagames. The primary combos of the deck are Copy Artifact loops, Mind Over Matter + The One Ring, and Mind Over Matter loops.
title: Tameshi Combo Control

commander.name: Etali, Primal Conqueror // Etali, Primal Sickness

description: Etali, Primal Conqueror is a outlet in the command zone with several different combos. Those combos include: Dockside Extortionist + Temur Sabertooth or Cloudstone Curio, Food Chain + Squee, the Immortal or Eternal Scourge, Dualcaster Mage + Twinflame or Heat Shimmer
title: Etali Combo

description: Stella Lee is a midrange combo Izzet deck which seeks to resolve Stella Lee as soon as possible before winning the game with one of her multiple tutorable 1 card combos. Stella Lee is unique among Izzet commanders in her 1 card combos are both tutorable and do not require playing a somewhat large package of build-around cards to make the deck work. This opens slots up for more generically powerful cards, making the deck powerful with Stella in play, but not reliant on her to function. Due to the instant speed nature of many of her combos, she also holds the capacity to win on top of your opponents through Borne Upon the Wind.
title: Stella Lee Turbo Threat

description: Narset, Enlightened Exile is truly one of Jeskai's strongest allies. This deck can be considered a 'turbo underworld breach' deck since Narset is seeking to win with underworld breach as quickly as possible. This is coupled with a disruptive graveyard strategy while utilizing cards like traumatize (a 1-card-win-condition) with Narset.
title: Narset Jeskai Breach

description: This is a proactive Simic deck that leverages its strong commander to set up insane value and combos to try to win early and grind late its effect being able to put lands into play untapped is so massive it's just a better Thrasios activation that's free if you can target your creatures and with clone effects when can reset out commanders passive it's very clear weakness is that it's a very commander-centric. With the 0 mana equip cards we can use them to get free activations and combo with cards like scute swarm and so much more.
title: [HISTORIC] Nadu Manual Value

description: This is a combo deck that aims to win at instant speed by targeting a copy spell on the stack with a second copy spell with the commander in play. This results in infinite Magecraft triggers, allowing us to rummage through the deck. In addition to being a combo engine, Ashling‚Äôs Magecraft abilities help us to sift through the deck, keep the board clear of dorks/hatebears, and ritual off while we are looking for wins.
title: Ashling Copy Storm

description: This deck leverages efficient creature combinations, usually including its flexible and resilient commander, Derevi, Empyrial Tactician. Derevi relishes the printings of Emiel, Preston, Delney, and Nadu, executes combos with artifacts like Birthing Pod and Chromatic Orrery, and employs The One Ring as an explosive card draw engine. Derevi's biggest weakness is not providing card advantage herself.
title: Derevi Midrange Pod

description: Glarb let's you play lands and cast spells (Mana Value 4+) from the top of library, which makes him good for grinding out the long game. You're much more likely than most decks to hit your land drop every turn, and the restriction on his ability to cast spells still lets you cast The One Ring or Ad Naus. He also turns all your top-of-deck tutors into immediately castable, often game-winning, cards. The main win condition (other than Thoracle) is Doomsday. We can Gush for free from the top to break the pile, or just Finale of Devastation X=2 for Thoracle, leaving 3 cards left exactly (Glarb can surveil 2 more if we need to). There are as many piles as there are board states (in theory).
title: Glarb DoomHulk

description: Dihada is a turbo deck with unique Breach Lines centered around Dihada, Binder of Wills. Dihada not only enables Breach Lines, but also fuels Reanimation strategies and allows you to have various tutor chains. After we have filled the yard, we can end the game in various ways. Her ability makes herself a great combo piece in Underworld Breach lines and also a great value piece giving your play more TURBO. Even if we reduce her abilities down to only one you will be surprised how versatile she is and how much impact she can have on the field. It is hard to break her down on only one strategy, we can choose between Underworld Breach, Ad Nauseam, Reanimation or even Doomsday (not in the deck currently). And the deck isn't overloaded because the strategies all evolve in parallel.
title: Dihada Breach

description: A deck that utilizes many Infinite mana combos to play it's commander as a sort of enchantment specific breach in esper that wants to win quickly after resolving many combos including Bomberman, Kitten teferi, Hullbreaker Horror, and Abdel loops to achieve infinite mana to be used to cast our commander, milling our library and reanimating thassa's oracle through an animate dead combo to win the game.
title: Master of Keys Enchantment Combo

description: Tivit is a primary cEDH Esper commander based around either a simple combo involving Tivit and Time Sieve, or a midrange grind plan produced by flickering Tivit with Displacer Kitten.
title: Tivit Midrange Combo

description: This is a midrange Esper deck using the commander to break parity in the long game by cheating out instant speed wins, uncounterable silences, or game-breaking creatures.
title: Hashaton Midrange Reanimator

description: A highly interactive Storm list that seeks to remain interactive throughout the game and win through a variety of Temur combos as well as by copying your opponents' best spells.
title: Storm Storm

description: Niv Mizzet Visionary deploys a plethora of burn engines and spells to draw massive amounts of cards, eventually assembling a typical Izzet combo or continuing to burn out opponents. Pingers, Bolt-effects, and strategies ranging from midrange to turbo can all be found in these lists.
title: Niv Mizzet Visionary Value

description: This variant of Esika is more of a NBC (No Bad Card) than the traditional Jeskai Ascendancy Storm or a polymorph variant. This variant is closer to a standard Blue Farm or RogSi deck than any other 5c Decks. The difference between a Blue Farm deck and Esika is that Esika is a mana engine in the command zone, while Tymna is a draw engine. Both decks utilize creatures like Ragavan and Lotho to generate advantage, however, Esika will utilize these creatures as an additional mana engine, hence the title, BoP Farm.
title: Esika 5C Good Stuff

decklists.title: You Don't Need Blue to Draw Cards

description: A turbo sacrifice deck focused on dumping your commander and creatures to create a sacrifice loop that inevitably wins the game in one of a few ways. You generally want to land the commander as soon as reasonably possible, with another creature or two available to sacrifice and start digging for cards. The biggest downfall is simply a Drannith Magistrate, since the deck plays out of exile. Upside is most of the combo pieces are creatures, making it less likely your opponents have a counterspell available for them.
title: Rakdos Sacrifice

description: This is a turbo deck that seeks to gain mana advantage through the commander and cast big spells to finish your opponents. But this deck is not only all-in turbo, as Rakdos is known for, it also can grind the midgame quite well.
title: Rowan Turbo Loss

description: Plagon, Lord of the Beach is a cEDH Azorius tempo storm shell that seeks to leverage the powerful draw engine in the command zone to accrue a ton of value. The deck plays like a traditional Azorius midrange/tempo deck in the beginning that seeks to eventually have a large storm turn to draw out your deck and win the game. There are typical and atypical win lines that layer tightly on top of each other; it's common to convert value engines into combo cards, and the deck rewards ingenuity to play at a top level. The deck's strengths lie in having overwhelming card draw, powerful stack control, and its ability to pivot off of its value pieces. Its weaknesses lie in being mana hungry, being in pretty mid colors (lacking good tutors), and having a below-average early game. However, the deck can mulligan generously, as Plagon will refill the cards in your hand that you mulliganed away.
title: Plagon Blink

description: This deck aims at joining the great pantheon of mono-green commander-centric decks like Yisan, Yeva, and Selvala. However, unlike those other commanders who have to be on the battlefield in order to get anything done, we don't need to worry about protecting our commander at all. In fact, this whole deck revolves around trying to get Lumra killed, like, a LOT. Since we can‚Äôt rely on our opponents to do this for us due to how enormous Lumra tends to get, we will have to take matters into our own lands cough I mean hands. Don‚Äôt be distracted by how big Lumra gets; having a 43/43 bear is certainly fun, but stay focused on the ultimate goal. The real path to victory lies in her ETB effect which allows us to manipulate our land count and their utility effects to win the game! Instead of swinging out for 21 commander damage, we win most consistently by pinging our opponents to death 1 tick of damage at a time.
title: Lumra Lands

description: An aggressive Mardu Dargo list focused on turbo-ing out Arena Rector then saccing it to Dargo, which starts a pod-style chain that puts Razaketh onto the battlefield to win. Dargo's depths as a combo piece, sac outlet, and facebeater create variety and unpredictability in both play patterns and wincons.
title: Dargo Tymna Turbo

description: An adaptive deck that either wins quickly with layered combos that run through Malcolm or transitions to a grindy control plan that uses both commanders to generate value before pushing through a win.
title: Izzet Malcolm

description: Niv-Mizz Parun Control, is a control shell similar to Rashmi, Curious Control, and Tasigur that seeks to slow the game down with Stax, prevent wins with interaction, and eventually end the game with a resolved Niv Mizzet. Compact combos include Curiosity effect on Niv-Mizzet, or sometimes with Glint-Horn Buccaneer or Isochron Scepter + Dramatic Reversal. Does poorly against multiple fast, low-interaction, decks. Does well against mid-range or other control lists.
title: Izzet Poly

description: Francisco Thrasios is a midrange deck that tries to use value engines to propel itself into the mid game, where it excels at winning over top of another opponent's win attempt. This is done by using Francisco and Walking Ballista combo to deal infinite damage at instant speed. We try to deploy draw engines in the early game to accrue value and sandbag protection. This deck's biggest strength is that, by using creature/artifact combos, we are hard to interact with. This deck's weakness is that we don't have access to white which would allow for stax to be able to build advantage in the early game.
title: Francisco Thrasios Midrange

description: This is a midrange deck that focuses on leveraging value from Krark flips without the need of clone effects or coin-flip doublers to find a way to victory. This means prioritizing powerful, low CMC cantrips, rituals, disruption spells, and tutors provided within the Grixis color identity. The deck has an abundance of powerful draw engines that allow grinding through the midgame. These include cards such as Archmage Emeritus, Mystic Remora, Yusri, Fortune's Flame, Rhystic Study and The One Ring.
title: Krark Silas Grixis Krark

description: Celes, Rune Knight is Mardu commander option with a strong ETB that can be used in infinite combos to draw the whole deck. This ETB can also be used to filter your hand to keep reanimation spells and to discard reanimation targets. Her second ability provides the possibility to win with persist creatures and a sac outlet with infinite sacrifices.
title: Celes Persistant Breach

description: Vivi is a commander that enables explosive storm turns, especially when combined with a curiosity effect. Vivi works both as a mana engine and as a combo outlet.
title: Vivi Curiosity Storm

description: Rydia is a proactive Gruul deck that seeks to use its low cost commander to rummage through its library aggressively, filling its graveyard and finding its combo pieces quickly. The deck wins using Ashaya, Soul of the Wilds & Quirion Ranger to infinitely rummage, Hedge Shredder & Golgari Grave-Troll to mill itself out, or various Underworld Breach lines, both Rydia-agnostic and her own unique versions.
title: Rydia Turbo Dredge

description: This deck is an adaptive temur midrange strategy, built around Loot, the Pathfinder. This deck's strategy is to leverage Loot's enormous utility in the command zone to out value and out politic everyone at the table. We are able to leverage loads of interaction, efficient card advantage engines, and multiple combo lines that win at instant speed to play around and over the top of your opponents. The deck is designed to function effectively with and without Loot on the battlefield using an array of combos such as Food Chain, Dualcaster Mage, and Hullbreaker Horror.
title: Loot Food Chain

description: Commonly referred to as WarDog, K-9/War Doc is a turbo-style Underworld Breach deck with a game plan to win early and has the ability to pivot based on the pilot's needs. It relies less on The War Doctor and leans more into synergies with K-9, Mark I to get us to The One Ring fastest (via Transmute Artifact) or the ability to use our free Commander-reliant interaction earlier.
title: War Doctor / K9 Turbo Breach

description: This deck is a five-color goodstuff list with a strong focus on enchantments. Terra, Magical Adept can adapt to both turbo and midrange strategies, performing reliably well in either approach. As a win condition, it can pivot to classic lines like Underworld Breach / Thassa's Oracle, or lean into its more unique identity with a Food Chain or clone loop using Terra‚Äôs back side. What sets this commander apart is the value engine it creates through milling and tutoring for enchantments.
title: Terra 5C Food Chain
